{"id": "duc04-testb-23:5#15", "contents": "The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has proposed a package deal to help Brazil address its financial crisis. However, this deal is contingent on the success of President Cardoso in persuading the legislature to implement unpopular austerity measures, primarily through cuts in social spending. These measures are crucial in reducing the country's huge deficits, which are a major contributor to the crisis. The IMF is keen to support Brazil, but only if the country demonstrates its commitment to fiscal discipline."}
